I"Y<p>Our PhD candidate <a href="https://3d.bk.tudelft.nl/biljecki">Filip Biljecki</a> participated in the <a href="http://summerschool.acrs2015.org/">13th ISPRS Summer School</a> held in in Quezon City, Philippines. The School was organised by the <a href="http://www.up.edu.ph">University of the Philippines</a>, the <a href="http://philgrss.org">Philippine Geosciences and Remote Sensing Society</a>, and the <a href="http://www.isprs-studentconsortium.org">ISPRS Student Consortium</a>. The topic of the event was “Using Geospatial Technologies for Natural Resources Management”, and it was collocated with the <a href="http://www.acrs2015.org">36th Asian Conference on Remote Sensing</a>. It contained lectures and workshops on a series of topics related to remote sensing and geoinformation.</p>

<p>The next <a href="http://www.isprs2016-prague.com/youth-activities/summer-school">ISPRS Summer School</a> will be held in Telč, Czech Republic. It will be a part of the <a href="http://www.isprs2016-prague.com">ISPRS XXIII Congress</a>.</p>

